narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned the language much more thoroughly than before. I also needed to cover material a lot more quickly than any course I have taken, so think my brain got used to remembering things at a faster pace.
I was introduced the basic structure of Latin grammar and the general method to deal with materials in Latin

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The front loading of the book makes the first couple weeks overwhelming. I felt pretty burnt out after that and found it hard to engage. The instructor Tim Robinson was wonderful though. His lessons were straightforward and included helpful background information. He created an environment in class that made it easy to speak up and ask questions.

I think this course was great at being able to understand actual texts very quickly, but it was also overwhelming when we rushed through the lecture on the unit and didn't cover most of the exercises in class. I would have appreciated more drills together in class.
The materials in class were well-stated and the daily exercise was clearly explained. But the pace was a little stressful for beginners, and we had limited time to review everyday.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, if you have to learn Latin fast
I would recommend this course, but only if someone is willing to put in the extra hours of work to cement what was learned in class.
Yes, especially for those who need to get familiar with Latin language in shorter time
